result.name: 一樂燒鵝

reviews.text: Had the Michelin Star Roast Goose at Yat Lok.  It is really a small shop that serves really good roast goose with caramelized skin. Their char siew is also quite good with a strong hint of Chinese wine.  However, be prepared to have a quick meal as the staff are super efficient to clearing your table.  Not a place where you linger and slowly enjoy your food.  Will not go there again unless I want an “eat and go” experience.

Try to avoid going to lunch or dinner peak hours else you might need to queue for quite a while. It’s Super pack inside thus sharing of tables can’t be avoided. 
Definitely try the roasted goose. Advisable to order half goose cut to enjoy the fullest.

Although the environment is not so good and it is too crowded inside the restaurant. I still have to give 5 stars regarding the price and the taste of the roast goose. If you don’t want to wait in line for more than half hour to have a nice roast goose, Yat-Lok should be the choice.
Very tasty!  Near central, easy to find.
They serve one of the best goose duck in town.

result.name: Yat Lok Roast Goose

reviews.text:
Came here as a group of 4, we reached around 5pm so it wasn't that crowded yet. The seats here are tight and the seating area is really limited so expect to squeeze quite closely to the table next to you. 

We ordered the famous roasted goose and was not disappointed! The meat was really tender and very flavorful, although it can get a little salty, it's really worth the money! 

Generally all the food served here were on the saltier side but it was really good.

Service was typical, due to the limited seating of the shop they would probably chase you out after you finish your food so don't expect to stay for long.

Totally rude!!! 
I know it got the michelin guide recommendations, but is that the reason you treat your paying customer as you like? Better go to Ki’s roast goose way better food and they treat you well.

My friend and I had a meal, when we had just finished our meal (probably 1 min after our last bite), my friend decided to go to toilet. So i waited in my seat. To my surprise, I was kicked out by the waiter and i was just asking 1 more minute to wait for my friend to come back, and the waitress asked me to get my friend’s bag and out of the restaurant and even said how heavy my friend’s bag going to be. I mean if you asked nicely, I would probably do it, at the end I am not unreasonable. Shame on you.. 

Come only if u want to be kicked out from a restaurant.

This place is way overrated. The goose is not that good, oily and skin not that crispy. Roast pork was quite nice with very crunchy skin. Food itself was not too bad, but there are much better places around. The downside is that since it is affiliated with Michelin (not sure if they even have a star) and is quite famous, it is a massive tourist trap. There is constantly a long line, and unlike other small unassuming Hong Kong restaurants in the Michelin guide, Yat Lok has jacked up the prices to ridiculous levels. Very disappointing

The roast goose here is good. But I think I had better. The place is very cramped too, and you could be made to split tables if you group is large. The owners will also chase you away when you are done with the meals even though your friends at the other table have not completed their meals yet. While it is understandable from the business point of view, but having a peace of mind before and after the meal is an equal important experience.

If you want sumptuous meal, this place is a must. I can't even describe well how I was impressed by their specialty, the roast goose. We went here as one famous vlogger highly recommends this place and there's not even a hint of regret as we are highly satisfied. Thumbs up!
